00:06:39.639 --> 00:06:48.139
Our fourth question is what scriptural example is there of a married couple who believe this one flesh idea?

00:06:48.839 --> 00:06:51.939
Turn to Romans chapter 16 and verse three, please.

00:06:51.939 --> 00:06:53.540
Romans 16, three.

00:06:55.240 --> 00:07:03.540
Here Paul writes, give my greetings to Priska or Priscilla and Aquila, my fellow workers in Christ Jesus.

00:07:03.540 --> 00:07:13.540
So yes, Aquila and Priscilla, what a model of a close and united couple living up to what Jehovah meant when he said that a husband or wife should become one flesh.

00:07:14.040 --> 00:07:22.040
And Paul who worked closely with them could not think of that dear brother without recalling the faithful cooperation of his wife.

00:07:22.040 --> 00:07:25.040
So it's a fine example for Christian couples today.

00:07:25.639 --> 00:07:37.939
And in every one of the six references to this couple in the Christian Greek scriptures, we find them working together, cooperating without competition or strife and never is one mentioned without the other.

00:07:38.639 --> 00:07:43.339
